Leaf Spot disease in maize plants, submitted to the inoculation
In the phytotoxicity essay, the non‐toxic concentrations were applied in the in vivo tests.
Phytotoxicity symptoms appeared after 12 h of the application on leaves. It was verified that at the
end of 10 days there was phytotoxicity in the concentrations of 7.5 μL mL
(20.9%), thus showing that cannot be utilized in tests of control of the disease in the
plant, provoking leaf necrosis, followed by posterior wilt. Yet the concentrations 2.5 μL mL
did not provoke phytotoxicity along the evaluation (Figure 2).
